<subSubSection id="89D86500FFB0FFFDFF7CA8AC5A89FAD1" pageId="7" pageNumber="612" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C17D368BFFB0FFFDFF7CA8AC5AF9FB5B" blockId="7.[167,777,899,1263]" pageId="7" pageNumber="612">
<emphasis id="F3B6EA99FFB0FFFDFF7CA8AC590AFC2F" bold="true" box="[168,285,899,923]" pageId="7" pageNumber="612">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body 
<quantity id="063A9B6EFFB0FFFDFEBCA8AC5A13FC2F" box="[360,516,899,923]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="612" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.6">5.60–6.50 mm</quantity>
long. Body elongate in shape. Dorsal coloration pale brown; pronotum darker on medial portion, with a pale brown medial line, suboval in shape. Prosternum not carinate. Mesoventral process laminar, slender, convex anteriorly, with acute tooth-like projection on anterior portion and concave on posterior margin in lateral view. Last abdominal ventrite deeply notched. Parameres wide, acuminate at apex, with long ventral setae on apical portion, membranous inner appendices present; median lobe slender, cylindrical, shorter than half of the parameres length, apices slightly bifid.
</paragraph>
